inputText: Generate a short poem about a bird and a butterfly
outputData:
In the heart of nature's grand design,
A bird and a butterfly, so divine. 

With wings of grace, the bird takes flight,
Into the vast and boundless daylight.
Its song echoes in the morning breeze,
A melody sculpted to please.

In hues of rainbow, the butterfly teases,
Dancing on flowers and the wind it seizes.
Its lightness whispers a delicate story,
Of nature's finesse and quiet glory.

Feathers and scales in a restless twirl, 
Paint a beautiful tapestry unfurl.
In this dance, both awe and inspire,
A symphony of life, never to tire.

Two tiny pieces of the wondrous wild,
In them, the heart of the universe beguiled.
A bird and a butterfly, in rhythm and rhyme,
Celebrate life, in the vast stream of time.
